name: Johnathan ROBINS, Petitioner v. Philadelphia County Court Judge The Honorable Charles J. CUNNINGHAM III, Respondent

parties: Johnathan ROBINS, Petitioner v. Philadelphia County Court Judge The Honorable Charles J. CUNNINGHAM III, Respondent.

opinions.text:
ORDER
PER CURIAM.
AND NOW, this 12th day of September, 2014, the Application for Leave to File Original Process is GRANTED, and the Petition for Writ of Mandamus is DENIED. The Prothonotary is directed to strike the name of the jurist from the caption.
opinions.author: PER CURIAM.

99 A.3d 534
Johnathan ROBINS, Petitioner v. Philadelphia County Court Judge The Honorable Charles J. CUNNINGHAM III, Respondent.

Sept. 12, 2014.
